// @run
// @log 0
// FIXED (ROADMAP A11: "mutual recursion across *separate* `type` decls"). This
// program is SOUND and now compiles: `type A` references `B` before `B` is
// declared, and `type B` references `A` — a cycle spanning two separate aliases.
//
// THE FIX: a top-level type-name pre-pass (`preRegisterTopLevelTypes`) hoists
// every `type` name into scope BEFORE any body is parsed, so a forward / mutual
// reference between alias bodies resolves to a lazy `Alias` leaf (carried by the
// name) instead of erroring "undeclared B". Both aliases then tie into one
// cycle-safe WasmGC rec-group, exactly like the single-self-recursive case.
//
// Kept under soundness/ as the regression anchor for the closed gap. A richer
// construct + traverse exercise lives in types/mutual-recursive-type.vl.
type A = { b: B | null }
type B = { a: A | null }
const x: A = { b: { a: null } }
// Reach across the A→B cycle: present `b`, then its `a` is null → 0.
if x.b != null {
  print(0)
}
